                            <comment id="14526315" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 4 May 2015 06:39:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user ehrmann opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/477&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/477&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3123&quot; title=&quot;Missing include in compiler/cpp/src/main.h breaks build in some environments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3123&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3123&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Include stdio.h to get a definition for FILE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    `FILE` is referenced on line 102 `extern FILE* yyin;`. I was cross compiling, and the definition for `FILE` not being included caused the build to fail, so I included it. I built again on Debian and FreeBSD, and it builds fine with the change&lt;/p&gt;

